{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644333"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:04:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:04:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18041"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18041","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18041"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.16,0.14,0.22,0.46]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10755"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74137"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10755","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10755"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18041"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59628"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1177"},{"type":"tags","id":"1919"},{"type":"tags","id":"2336"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"6625"},{"type":"tags","id":"7871"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25089"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25092"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74137"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old woman presents to the haematology clinic with fatigue and recurrent infections over the past three months. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears pale with a pulse rate of 90/min, blood pressure 120/80 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. There is no lymphadenopathy or hepatosplenomegaly. Laboratory investigations reveal pancytopenia. A bone marrow biopsy is performed.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following describes the appearance of the bone marrow on histology in this condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Normocellular with increased megakaryocytes","Hypocellular with fibrosis","Hypercellular with lymphoid infiltration","Hypercellular with myeloid hyperplasia","Hypocellular with increased fat spaces"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms and laboratory findings suggestive of aplastic anaemia, a condition characterised by pancytopenia due to bone marrow failure. The bone marrow biopsy in aplastic anaemia typically shows a \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypocellular marrow with increased fat spaces\u003C/strong\u003E, reflecting the replacement of haematopoietic tissue with fat.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypercellular with myeloid hyperplasia\u003C/strong\u003E would be expected in conditions such as chronic myeloid leukaemia, where there is an overproduction of myeloid cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypercellular with lymphoid infiltration\u003C/strong\u003E is characteristic of lymphoid leukaemias or lymphomas, where malignant lymphoid cells infiltrate the bone marrow.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormocellular with increased megakaryocytes\u003C/strong\u003E might be seen in conditions like essential thrombocythaemia, where there is an overproduction of platelets.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypocellular with fibrosis\u003C/strong\u003E is indicative of myelofibrosis, where the bone marrow is replaced by fibrous tissue, leading to pancytopenia and extramedullary haematopoiesis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Bone marrow histology can reveal important information about haematological disorders.","Aplastic anaemia is characterised by a hypocellular bone marrow with increased fat spaces.","Leukaemia often presents with hypercellular bone marrow due to infiltration by malignant cells."],"references":["Gartner, L. P. (2020). Textbook of histology e-book: Textbook of histology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Baig MA, Bacha D. Histology, Bone. 2023 May 1. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31082176","Blumer MJF. Bone tissue and histological and molecular events during development of the long bones. Ann Anat. 2021 May;235:151704. doi: 10.1016/j.aanat.2021.151704. Epub 2021 Feb 16. PMID: 33600952","Florencio-Silva R, Sasso GR, Sasso-Cerri E, Sim\u00f5es MJ, Cerri PS. Biology of Bone Tissue: Structure, Function, and Factors That Influence Bone Cells. Biomed Res Int. 2015;2015:421746. doi: 10.1155/2015/421746. Epub 2015 Jul 13. PMID: 26247020; PMCID: PMC4515490","Peslak SA, Olson T, Babushok DV. Diagnosis and Treatment of Aplastic Anemia. Curr Treat Options Oncol. 2017 Nov 16;18(12):70. doi: 10.1007/s11864-017-0511-z. PMID: 29143887; PMCID: PMC5804354.","Furlong E, Carter T. Aplastic anaemia: Current concepts in diagnosis and management. J Paediatr Child Health. 2020 Jul;56(7):1023-1028. doi: 10.1111/jpc.14996. Epub 2020 Jul 3. PMID: 32619069."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59628"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18041"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59628","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59628"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T21:29:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T22:12:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10755"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74137"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"13","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api